A total of six people sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate in a crash between two motor vehicles in Durban on Friday night. DURBAN - Six people were injured in a traffic collision involving two cars on Friday, according to reports by Netcare 911. Late in the evening, emergency responders were called to a collision on the N3 Durban-bound before the Pavillion Shopping Centre in the Durban West region. READ: N14 collision kills four people Two vehicles were involved in a collision resulting in a bakkie landing on its roof, according to reports from the scene. Six people sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate and were treated preliminarily before being transported by ambulance to a nearby hospital for further treatment.